"Overall - I generally believe that quads don't need to be barreled, but if you're going to do it, this is a textbook example of how. Restrained barreling that adds to and doesn't overpower a solid quad. If a bit alcoholic, I love that complex profile, espexially the toasted oak and yeast spice balancing the sweetness."
