"I'm sorry but this beer isn't to style. This beer isn't good.  It's 14 dollars a bottle which is a joke.  If you LOVE overly sweet and non complex flavors this might be worth a try.  For all else run."
"The aroma conjures the taste of caramel, creamy vanilla, cranberries, and some nice raisin. A good balance of bourbon, tartness, brown bread, and earthiness summarizes the flavor appropriately. A sweet black cherry addition is very enjoyable. The finish is a tad herbal and sharp, with perhaps a bit of a clove element to it as well. Although the body and mouth feel are moderately light, the warming sensation is heavy... and in this case, it's quite welcome. I don't think anyone who seeks out a BBA Quad is looking for an easy- drinking beer! Overall, this is a memorable entry in the style.  A note to future drinkers and in reference to other reviewers: It's essential to enjoy this beer chilled, slightly above room temperature. If you try to have it right out of the fridge the flavors do not come through properly; you are not getting the correct experience out of it."
""
""
"Overall: While interesting, and the only Clown Shoes beer other than Vampire Slayer that I did not find to be a single-note assault of hops like Marine mechanized infantry pouring out of an APC with guns blazing, I don't know that this is a repeater for me. The barrel notes were anything but subtle, and the quad flavors were 100% ester with little to no malt evident. Still, a decent beer."
