"Overall, the aroma of this is inviting, but the richness and stickiness accompanied by so much sweet candy like flavors just doesn't do it for me. I'd like a little more bourbon character."
"22 ounce bottle into chalice, bottled on 12/16/2014. Pours slightly hazy dark ruby red color with a 1 finger fairly dense khaki head with poor retention, that reduces to nothing pretty quickly. Minimal lacing on the glass, with some light streaming carbonation. Aromas of big raisin, plum, fig, date, caramel, toffee, toast, candi sugar, pepper, clove, oak, light bourbon, light vanilla, and yeast/oak earthiness. Damn nice aromas with good balance and complexity of fruity/spicy yeast, dark malt, and light-moderate barrel notes; with good strength. Taste of big raisin, plum, fig, date, caramel, toffee, toast, candi sugar, pepper, clove, oak, light bourbon, light vanilla, and yeast/oak earthiness. Fair amount of yeast spiciness on the finish; with lingering notes of raisin, plum, fig, date, caramel, toffee, toast, candi sugar, pepper, clove, oak, bourbon, vanilla, and yeast/oak earthiness on the finish for a while. Fantastic complexity and robustness of dark malt, fruity/spicy yeast, and light-moderate bourbon barrel flavors; with a great malt/yeast/barrel balance and zero cloying flavors after the finish. Medium carbonation and medium-full bodied; with a very smooth and lightly slick mouthfeel that is nice. Alcohol is very well hidden with only a light warming present after the finish. Overall this is a very excellent quadrupel style. All around great complexity and balance of dark malt, fruity/spicy yeast, and light-moderate bourbon barrel flavors; and very smooth to sip on for the huge ABV. A very enjoyable offering."
